  "title": "supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Recognized Tertiary\n     qualification in Diploma or related discipline</li><li>At least three (3) years’\n     relevant project management experience in the area of project management\n     for system related works;</li><li>Proficient in programmed planning\n     software such as Microsoft Project for Windows;</li><li>Strong analytical and\n     problem-solving skills, resourceful and meticulous;</li><li>Highly motivated and\n     pro-active with the ability to work both independently as well as in a\n     team;</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office\n     (Outlook, Word, Excel and PowerPoint) for Windows;</li><li>Good verbal communication\n     and writing skills in English;</li><li>Be expected to travel\n     regularly between office and sites;</li><li>Perform night work based on\n     project needs; and</li><li>Possess Class 3 driving\n     license is preferred.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and execute the\n     operations projects with multiple project engineers and managers within\n     the work place.</li><li>Responsible for project\n     functions included but not limited to Site Management, Control Management,\n     Procurement, Construction Management, etc. are all coordinated and\n     properly staffed to meet the project.</li><li>Ensure accurate and timely\n     reporting standards are maintained throughout the project.</li><li>Establish the working\n     relationship with operations management needed to facilitate the coordination\n     and execution of project work, such that the operational impact is\n     minimized.</li><li>Monitor engineering progress\n     against budget and forecasted schedule.</li></ul>",
